---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '../../components/Sidebar.astro';
const title = "Diamantopoulos et al. (2026) - X-ray PSD energy dependence - ArXiv Atlas";

import WikiLink from '../../components/WikiLink.astro';
---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">Energy dependence of the X-ray power spectrum in NGC4051 and NGC4395</h1>
        
        <div class="paper-meta">
            <p><strong>Authors:</strong> V. A. Diamantopoulos, I. E. Papadakis, A. Akylas, A. Zoghbi, E. Kammoun, B. Rani</p>
            <p><strong>arXiv ID:</strong> <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11825" target="_blank">2603.11825</a></p>
            <p><strong>Date:</strong> 2026-03-12</p>
            <p><strong>Status:</strong> A&amp;A, 707, A180 (2026)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="abstract-box">
            <h3>Abstract</h3>
            <p>Using XMM-Newton, Suzaku, and NuSTAR data, the authors compute PSDs in six energy bands (0.3--20 keV) for NGC4051 and NGC4395 and fit bending power-law models. They report energy-independent bending frequencies, flattening high-frequency slopes at harder energies, and decreasing PSD amplitude with energy<sup><a href="#ref1">1</a></sup>.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="section-0">Key Results</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>PSD bending frequency consistent across energy bands (energy-independent)<sup><a href="#ref1">1</a></sup>.</li>
            <li>High-frequency slope flattens at higher photon energies<sup><a href="#ref1">1</a></sup>.</li>
            <li>PSD amplitude decreases with increasing energy (less fractional variability at hard X-rays)<sup><a href="#ref1">1</a></sup>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="section-1">Implications</h2>
        <p>These findings constrain models of X-ray variability (e.g., the fluctuating accretion-rate model) and suggest energy-dependent variability mechanisms across different coronal/emission regions<sup><a href="#ref1">1</a></sup>.</p>

        <h2 id="section-2">References</h2>
        <ol class="references">
            <li id="ref1">Diamantopoulos, V. A., Papadakis, I. E., Akylas, A., et al. (2026). "Energy dependence of the X-ray power spectrum in NGC4051 and NGC4395." <em>A&amp;A</em>, 707, A180. DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1051/0004-6361/202557606">10.1051/0004-6361/202557606</a> (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11825">arXiv:2603.11825</a>).</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="page-tags">
            <strong>Tags:</strong>
            <WikiLink slug="pages/Tag_Xray" text="X-ray" />
